  "text": "• Property 1. (Theorem 8 in [CITATION_1] and Theorem 1 in [CITATION_2] ) If σ > 4 in (3), then, even if the sampling continues forever, the total number of local searches ever started by MLSL is finite with probability 1. • Property 2. (Theorem 12 in [CITATION_3] and Theorem 2 in [CITATION_4] ) If r k tends to 0 with increasing k, then any local minimum x * will be found within a finite number of iterations with probability 1.",
